X_n \rightarrow X
\Pr \{ \lim X_n = X \} = 1
\forall \varepsilon > 0
N > 0
\forall n > N
\Pr \{ \omega : | X_n ( \omega) - X ( \omega) | < \varepsilon \} = 1
\Pr \{ \omega : | X_n ( \omega) - X ( \omega) | > \varepsilon \} = 0
\varepsilon > 0
N > 0
n > N
 \bigcup_{\varepsilon > 0} \bigcap_{N = 0}^{\infty} \bigcup_{n = N}^{\infty}    \{ \omega : | X_n ( \omega) - X ( \omega) | > \varepsilon \} 
 \bigcup_{m = 1}^{\infty} \bigcap_{N = 0}^{\infty} \bigcup_{n = N}^{\infty}    \left\{ \omega : | X_n ( \omega) - X ( \omega) | > \frac{1}{m} \right\} 
 B_t=\bigcap_{N = 0}^{\infty} \bigcup_{n = N}^{\infty}    \{ \omega : | X_n ( \omega) - X ( \omega) | > t \}.  
